{"content":"---\ntitle: \"<activityStateQuery>\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.topic: \"reference\"\nms.assetid: 9f8c3e4f-e2e3-4402-9760-03bf918ece7b\n---\n# \\<activityStateQuery>\nRepresents a query that is used to track life cycle changes of the activities that make up a workflow instance. For example, you may want to keep track of every time the \"Send E-Mail\" activity completes within a workflow instance. This query is necessary for a tracking participant to subscribe to activity state record objects. The available states to subscribe to are specified in ActivityStates.  \n  \n For more information on tracking profile queries, see [Tracking Profiles](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/tracking-profiles.md).  \n  \n\\<system.serviceModel>  \n\\<tracking>  \n\\<trackingProfile>  \n\\<workflow>  \n\\<activityStateQueries>  \n\\<activityStateQuery>  \n  \n## Syntax  \n  \n```xml\n<tracking>\n  <trackingProfile name=\"Name\">\n    <workflow>\n      <activityStateQueries>\n        <activityStateQuery activityName=\"String\" />\n        <arguments>\n          <argument name=\"String\"/>\n        </arguments>\n        <states>\n          <state name=\"String\"/>\n        </states>\n        <variables>\n          <variable name=\"String\"/>\n        </variables>\n      </activityStateQueries>\n    </workflow>\n  </trackingProfile>\n</tracking>  \n```  \n  \n## Attributes and Elements  \n The following sections describe attributes, child elements, and parent elements.  \n  \n### Attributes  \n  \n|Attribute|Description|  \n|---------------|-----------------|  \n|activityName|A string that specifies the name of the activity to filter <xref:System.Activities.Tracking.ActivityStateRecord> instances on.|  \n  \n### Child Elements  \n  \n|Element|Description|  \n|-------------|-----------------|  \n|[\\<arguments>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/windows-workflow-foundation/arguments.md)|A collection of arguments associated with this activity query.|  \n|[\\<states>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/windows-workflow-foundation/states.md)|A collection of configuration elements that contain the states of the subscribed activity for which a tracking record should be emitted.|  \n|[\\<states>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/windows-workflow-foundation/states.md)|A collection of variables associated with this activity query.|  \n  \n### Parent Elements  \n  \n|Element|Description|  \n|-------------|-----------------|  \n|[\\<faultPropagationQuery>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/windows-workflow-foundation/faultpropagationquery.md)|Represents a list of configuration elements that are used to track requests to cancel a child activity by the parent activity. The query is necessary for a tracking participant to subscribe to cancel request record objects.|  \n  \n## Remarks  \n One unique feature of an ActivityStateQuery is the ability to extract data when tracking the execution of a workflow. This provides additional context when accessing the tracking records post execution. You can use the [\\<arguments>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/windows-workflow-foundation/arguments.md), [\\<states>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/windows-workflow-foundation/states.md) and [\\<states>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/windows-workflow-foundation/states.md) elements to extract any variable or argument from any activity in a workflow. The following example shows an activity state query that extracts variables and arguments when the activityâ€™s `Closed` tracking record is emitted. Variables and arguments can be extracted only with an ActivityStateRecord and thus are subscribed to within a tracking profile using [\\<activityStateQuery>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/windows-workflow-foundation/activitystatequery.md).  \n  \n```xml  \n<activityStateQuery activityName=\"SendEmailActivity\">  \n  <states>  \n    <state name=\"Closed\"/>  \n  </states>  \n  <variables>  \n    <variable name=\"FromAddress\"/>  \n  </variables>  \n  <arguments>  \n    <argument name=\"Result\"/>  \n  </arguments>  \n</activityStateQuery>  \n```  \n  \n## See also\n\n- <xref:System.ServiceModel.Activities.Tracking.Configuration.ActivityStateQueryElement?displayProperty=nameWithType>\n- <xref:System.Activities.Tracking.ActivityStateQuery?displayProperty=nameWithType>\n- [Workflow Tracking and Tracing](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/workflow-tracking-and-tracing.md)\n- [Tracking Profiles](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/tracking-profiles.md)\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,126],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"<activityStateQuery>\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.topic: \"reference\"\nms.assetid: 9f8c3e4f-e2e3-4402-9760-03bf918ece7b","nodes":[{"content":"<activityStateQuery>","nodes":[],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[133,154],"content":"\\<activityStateQuery>","linkify":"\\<activityStateQuery>","nodes":[{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>activityStateQuery&gt;","pos":[0,21],"source":"\\<activityStateQuery>"}]},{"content":"Represents a query that is used to track life cycle changes of the activities that make up a workflow instance.","pos":[155,266]},{"content":"For example, you may want to keep track of every time the \"Send E-Mail\" activity completes within a workflow instance.","pos":[267,385]},{"content":"This query is necessary for a tracking participant to subscribe to activity state record objects.","pos":[386,483]},{"content":"The available states to subscribe to are specified in ActivityStates.","pos":[484,553]},{"pos":[560,714],"content":"For more information on tracking profile queries, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Tracking Profiles<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/tracking-profiles.